folder: 125th Street (West) & St. Nicholas Avenue, Manhattan, NY
text:
West 125th Street, south side, west from St. Nicholas, to and including Morningside Aves. Shown is the West End Theatre, at Nos. 362-370, built in 1902 by Weber and Fields. ( originally a vaudeville house and now used for motion pictures) July 27, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.
